1.Given an array arr[] consisting of n integers, the task is to find all the array elements which occurs more than floor(n/3) times.
Platform : GeeksForGeeks
SOURCE CODE :class Solution {
    public ArrayList<Integer> findMajority(int[] arr) {
        // Code here
        Arrays.sort(arr);
        ArrayList<Integer> list=new ArrayList<>();
        int n=arr.length;
        int count=1;
        for(int i=1;i<n;i++){
            if(arr[i]==arr[i-1]){
                count++;
            }
            else{
                if(count>n/3){
                    list.add(arr[i-1]);
                }
                count=1;
            }
        }
        if(count>n/3){
            list.add(arr[n-1]);
        }
        return list;
    }
}
Link : https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/problems/majority-vote/1
2.Given an array arr[]. Find the majority element in the array. If no majority element exists, return -1.
Platform : GeeksForGeeks
SOURCE CODE : class Solution {
    public int majorityElement(int[] nums) {
        int candidate = 0;
        int count = 0;

        for (int num : nums) {
            if (count == 0) {
                candidate = num;
            }

            if (num == candidate) {
                count++;
            } else {
                count--;
            }
        }

        count = 0;
        for (int num : nums) {
            if (num == candidate) {
                count++;
            }
        }

        return (count > nums.length / 2) ? candidate : -1;
    }
}
Link : https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/problems/majority-element-1587115620/1
3.Given an integer n. Write a program to find the first prime number greater than n.
Platform : GeeksForGeeks
SOURCE CODE : class Solution {
    public static int nextPrime(int n) {

        // code here to find next prime number
        // return next prime number
        for(int i=n+1;i<=500;i++){
            boolean isPrime=true;
            for(int j=2;j<=Math.sqrt(i);j++){
                if(i%j==0){
                    isPrime=false;
                }
            }
            if(isPrime){
                return i;
            }
        }
        return -1;
    }
}
